latestPosts.caption:
R.I.S.H.I.K.E.S.H. ❤️

This place needs no introduction. In 1968, the English rock band - the Beatles studied meditation here as students of Maharishi Mahesh Yogi, who devised the Transcendental Meditation technique. It is said that it was the band’s most productive period as songwriters. Today, popularly known as the “Beatles Ashram” it serves as one of the major tourist attractions in Rishikesh with its beautiful paintings and foregone vibes 😍

One of the quotes written on the walls “Pursuing Individualism” got me thinking deeply ✨

#rishikesh_diaries #rishikesh #uttarakhandheaven #india #sukoon

latestPosts.caption:
Your third @ needs to take you here 😍🇹🇭

Hidden in the lush corners of Chiang Rai, Lalitta Café is not just a café — it’s a dreamy escape into a fantasy forest.
With misty waterfalls, fairytale sculptures, and whimsical garden paths, every corner here feels like you’re in a magical movie set 🥰

The coffee’s great, almost negligible veg food options, waiting time could be longer but the views and the vibes just make up for everything ✨😍

🕘 Open daily from 8 AM to 8 PM

💸 Entry is 60 Baht pp (redeemable on food & drinks)

📍 Lalitta Cafe, Chiang Rai

Pro Tip: Get there early! This place gets crowded as the day goes on — and trust me, it’s way more magical when it’s quiet.

latestPosts.caption:
You know whom to share this with 😋

Just 40 km from Bangkok stands Wat Samphran – a 17-storey pink cylindrical tower wrapped by a massive dragon sculpture 🏯🐲. This offbeat spot isn’t just jaw-dropping — it’s deeply spiritual.

🧘‍♂️ The temple was envisioned by a monk in meditation and is unlike any other in Thailand — combining Buddhist philosophy with surreal architecture.

🚶‍♀️ Yes, you can climb inside the dragon through a tunnel-like path spiraling to the top — it’s a little spooky, but the view is totally worth it!

📍 Location: Wat Samphran, Nakhon Pathom (1 hr from Bangkok) (Hire a taxi or ride a scooter yourself. Public transport may be difficult to reach here)

🕘 Timings: 9 AM – 5 PM

💸 Entry Fee: Free but they will ask for money as donations which is almost mandatory (consider about THB 100 pp i.e. INR 27-300 pp)

👚 Dress Code: Modest (shoulders & knees covered)

✨ This isn’t your typical tourist spot — it’s a hidden gem that’s equally photogenic and powerful. Add this to your Bangkok day trip list!

#bangkok #dragontemple #hiddengemsbangkok #thailand_ig #thailandtravel #trendingréels

When vibes are vibing 😌😍

The cafe culture in Thailand will leave you spellbound. It’s not just a cafe but an entrance to a very magical and mysterious world. So while you sip on amazing coffee and delicious food, you get to be amidst nature, filled with greenery, fog, waterfalls, and fish ponds. We had veg Pad Thai which was absolutely the best! 

📍Chom Cafe, Chiang Mai, Thailand

When the weather passes the vibe check 😍

There’s something about the monsoon that hits different. The scent of wet earth, the sound of raindrops tapping against windows, the way the wind carries both a chill and a strange warmth. It slows you down, pulls you into the present. The world looks softer, hearts feel heavier and lighter at the same time.

That’s the thing about monsoons—they don’t just change the weather; they change you. 🌧️🫶🏼
